@startuml
title Creating and Running a Window - Beginner Flow

skinparam ParticipantPadding 8

actor "User code" as User
participant "Application" as App
participant "WindowHandle" as Handle
participant "Widget tree" as Widgets
participant "Sparkle runtime" as Runtime

User -> App : create Application
User -> App : createWindow(id, rect/title)
App --> User : WindowHandle
User -> Handle : centralWidget()
Handle --> User : root widget
User -> Widgets : add child widgets or customize behavior

User -> App : run()
activate App
loop while the app is running
	Runtime -> Widgets : deliver input events
	Runtime -> Widgets : update(UpdateTick)
	Runtime -> Widgets : collect render commands
	Runtime -> Runtime : draw and present
end
App --> User : exit code
deactivate App

note right of Handle
User code normally keeps WindowHandle,
not the internal Window object.
end note

@enduml
